  "prompt": "How do you know if it's love or infatuation?",
  "response": "Here are some key differences between love and infatuation:\n\nLove typically involves:\n1. Deep emotional connection\n2. Commitment and long-term care\n3. Acceptance of flaws\n4. Mutual respect\n5. Desire for partner's happiness\n6. Emotional intimacy\n7. Consistent feelings over time\n\nInfatuation often includes:\n1. Intense physical/sexual attraction\n2. Idealization of the person\n3. Obsessive thoughts\n4. Short-term excitement\n5. Focus on physical/surface qualities\n6. Emotional volatility\n7. Feelings tend to fade quickly\n\nSigns it might be love:\n- You want to support their goals\n- You can imagine a future together\n- You feel comfortable being yourself\n- You're willing to work through challenges\n- Your feelings remain steady\n\nSigns it might be infatuation:\n- Primarily physical attraction\n- Dramatic, roller-coaster emotions\n- Unrealistic expectations\n- More fantasy than reality\n- Lack of deep understanding\n\nEach relationship is unique, but these general guidelines can help distinguish between temporary infatuation and genuine love.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these points?",
